          "logprobs": [],
          "text": "On March 2, 2026, NVIDIA Corporation (NVDA) executives received significant performance-based stock awards, as reported in SEC Form 4 filings:\n\n- **Jen-Hsun Huang, CEO**: Granted 936,771 shares, comprising 179,411 shares vesting over four years and 757,360 shares vesting fully on March 18, 2026. ([stocktitan.net](https://www.stocktitan.net/sec-filings/NVDA/form-4-nvidia-corp-insider-trading-activity-9f3a2a888227.html?utm_source=openai))\n\n- **Debora Shoquist, Executive Vice President of Operations**: Received 98,328 shares, with one award vesting over four years and another fully vesting on March 18, 2026. ([stocktitan.net](https://www.stocktitan.net/sec-filings/NVDA/form-4-nvidia-corp-insider-trading-activity-60eb478aba6c.html?utm_source=openai))\n\n- **Colette Kress, Chief Financial Officer**: Awarded 106,660 shares, with one award vesting over four years and another fully vesting on March 18, 2026. ([stocktitan.net](https://www.stocktitan.net/sec-filings/NVDA/form-4-nvidia-corp-insider-trading-activity-024e5a93b734.html?utm_source=openai))\n\n- **Ajay K. Puri, Executive Vice President of Worldwide Field Operations**: Granted 103,278 shares, with one award vesting over four years and another fully vesting on March 18, 2026. ([stocktitan.net](https://www.stocktitan.net/sec-filings/NVDA/form-4-nvidia-corp-insider-trading-activity-53ef267eee54.html?utm_source=openai))\n\nThese grants reflect NVIDIA's commitment to aligning executive compensation with company performance and shareholder value.\n\n## Stock market information for NVIDIA Corp (NVDA)\n- NVIDIA Corp is a equity in the USA market.\n- The price is 175.64 USD currently with a change of 2.98 USD (0.02%) from the previous close.\n- The latest open price was 177.38 USD and the intraday volume is 182836294.\n- The intraday high is 178.32 USD and the intraday low is 170.5 USD.\n- The latest trade time is Monday, March 23, 17:15:00 PDT.\n "
